    "componentChoices": "The design leverages existing app components for consistency and familiarity.  List items are used to display settings with clear labels. Toggles are used for boolean settings, while links are used for actions requiring additional context or navigation.  The appbar and bottom navigation components ensure consistent branding and user experience.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through the use of a vertical list, with the most critical settings listed first.  Text styles (Headline, Title, Body) and color styles (Primary, Secondary, Tertiary) are used to guide the user's attention and establish prominence.  Visual indicators highlight active/inactive states for clarity.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "List item variants are selected based on content provided. For settings with a trailing action (toggle or link), the `Trailing` variant is used with the appropriate action type (`Switch` for toggles). For settings that do not require secondary actions, the `Trailing` variant is set to `None`.  `Headline` text style is used for primary titles, `Body/Medium` for settings text. Color styles are consistently used to ensure visual clarity."
  }
